Commentary Text: Boult to Finch, out Caught by Pollard!! Catching practice for Pollard at long-off - the threatening partnership has been broken. Change of pace and Finch was done in completely - the slower ball and Finch had to manufacture all the pace on this attempted lofted drive - was looking to go over cover, but it skewed off the inner half and lobbed down towards Pollard at long-off. Commentary Text: Udana to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by de Villiers!! RCB have two now. They had a solitary wicket in the powerplay before today and that too a lucky dismissal of Warner and now they have two in the space of four balls. Short of length delivery angled across the right hander, the ball bounces more than Suryakumar anticipated, he goes for the steer and edges it behind to the keeper. AB has a juggle before completing the catch. Suryakumar Yadav c de Villiers b Udana 0(2)

Commentary Text: Washington Sundar to Rohit, out Caught by (sub)Negi!! First time Sundar has opened the bowling this season and he has got the big wicket of Rohit. Just the start RCB wanted especially after an expensive over from Udana. Rohit had enough of defending and was looking to go for the biggie, the length was fraction short and he was quick to pounce, pulls it high and that would have gone the distance in any other ground but not in Dubai, Negi settles under it at deep mid-wicket and hangs on comfortably. Rohit c (sub)Negi b Washington Sundar 8(8) [6s-1]
